{"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/setenv(variable:value:overwrite:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"setenv","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"variable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"value","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"overwrite"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that on some systems, when variables are overwritten, the memory"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"used for the previous variables and its value isn’t reclaimed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You should be mindful of the fact that environment variable handling","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in UNIX is not thread-safe, and your program may crash if one thread"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calls "},{"code":"g_setenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" while another thread is calling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"getenv()"},{"text":". (And note","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that many functions, such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gettext()"},{"type":"text","text":", call "},{"code":"getenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" internally.)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This function is only safe to use at the very start of your program,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"before creating any other threads (or creating objects that create"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"worker threads of their own).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to set up the environment for a child process, you can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_get_environ()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to get an environment array, modify that with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_environ_setenv()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_unsetenv()"},{"text":", and then pass that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"array directly to "},{"code":"execvpe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_spawn_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or the like.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/setenv(variable:value:overwrite:)"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setenv","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"variable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"value"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseI